-2} (1.3 {\\rm mm}/\\lambda)$ cm$^2$ g$^{-1}$\nadvocated by Beckwith et al. (1990). We inferred a temperature of ~45K at the\ndisk outer edge which increases radially inward. It is well above the\nsublimation temperatures of ices such as CO and N$_2$, which supports the\nnotion that the disk chemistry cannot be completely inherited from the\nprotostellar envelope.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Aug 2020 18:40:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 22 Dec 2021 17:14:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-23"}
